- "longest-running voyages" refers to the experiments with the highest average trial duration;
- "child explorers" is a metaphor for children participating in the experiments;
- "top three exploratory endeavors" refers to the highest-ranked experiments based on average trial duration within each age group;
- "age group" refers to the age of children in the database.
